Rating: 4
Delicious recipe, but I think the instructions are written poorly. I used 3 T flour and added this to the butter to make a roux, cooking it until dark golden brown. Then I whisked in the broth, then wine, and rest of ingredients. I think the order is very important, as well as adding the ingredients slowly while whisking to prevent clumping. This also took about 2 hours to fully reduce. I uncovered the pot and turned up the heat at the end, and the resulting sauce was DELICIOUS. Will definitely make again, since it's so easy once it's covered and simmering.

Rating: 3
Made and served a double recipe of this dish for a birthday party. Everyone loved the mushrooms. Only reason it rates 3 forks is because I had to adjust. Needs at least twice as much worcestershire sauce and a decent amount of salt and pepper to have good flavor. Also, cooked in a slow cooker which worked well. I suggest following recipe and then add additional worcestershire sauce to taste. Overall, it was a hit.

